        <h2>About Me</h2>
<p><h6 align="center">Nwachukwu Clinton Nnamdi (born 27 November 1996), who is known professionally as FortiRoq,is a Nigerian Blockchain Developer. Born in the Parakou suburb of Benin Republic, FortiRoq is a voice in the emerging CTNG movement. His DeFi Academy is a blend of Web3, DeFi, Web3 Jobs, NFTs, Metaverse,DeFi Protocols and Narratives, GameFi and Marketing/Influencing. He began trading the crypto market at the age of 24 and released a collaborative partnership with the Kashflow, FortiRoq Inc. and a couple of his Indiano American friends. In 2021, FortiRoq signed a Marketing specialist, Community manager, Project Advisory deal with MiFunder Prop Firm and other Crypto Projects. He rose to the limelight after releasing FortiRoq DeFi Academy at Tanzania, Cameroon and Ghana. The lead from his affiliations in Nigeria CTNG, which also spawned the collaborations Tanzanian Crypto Community and Other Countries.</h6></p>
